Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

I think this patch is good, but I see an error in the test output in the suite_log, at  https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1783225a-0a57-11ea-9487-52540065bddc:
if [ \$running -eq 0 ] ; then
	mkdir -p /mnt/lustre;
	mount -t lustre  -o user_xattr,flock,skpath=/dev/null trevis-47vm4@tcp:/lustre /mnt/lustre;
	rc=\$?;
fi;
exit \$rc
Invalid shared key path: /dev/null
mount.lustre: Error loading shared keys: Unknown error -126

I only see this for the test that was modified in this patch, test 29. The skpath in mount is /dev/null. Is this expected?
